        "assistant": "“Off-token route” and “embodied cognition” are different concepts from different domains.\n\n### Off-token route\n\nAn **off-token route** is usually an AI/software idea: a processing path that happens **outside the normal token stream**.\n\nIn an LLM system, “tokens” are pieces of text. So an off-token route might involve:\n\n- tool calls\n- database queries\n- search/retrieval\n- image/audio processing\n- routing logic\n- hidden backend computation\n- API calls not expressed directly in the model’s text output\n\nExample:\n\n> Instead of answering from text tokens alone, the system sends the request to a calculator through an off-token route.\n\nIt is mainly about **system architecture**.\n\n---\n\n### Embodied cognition\n\n**Embodied cognition** is a theory in cognitive science saying that cognition is deeply shaped by the body’s interaction with the world.\n\nIt emphasizes that thinking is not just abstract symbol manipulation in the brain. It is influenced by:\n\n- perception\n- movement\n- bodily states\n- spatial orientation\n- sensorimotor experience\n- interaction with the physical environment\n\nExample:\n\n> Understanding “grasping an idea” may be partly related to bodily experience with grasping physical objects.\n\nIt is mainly about **how minds understand and think through bodies and environments**.\n\n---\n\n### Main difference\n\n| Concept | Main idea | Domain |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Off-token route** | Processing happens outside text-token flow | AI/software systems |\n| **Embodied cognition** | Thought is grounded in bodily experience and action | Cognitive science/philosophy/psychology |\n\n### Simple version\n\nAn **off-token route** is about **where computation happens in an AI system**.\n\n**Embodied cognition** is about **how cognition is shaped by having a body in the world**.\n\nAn AI system could have off-token routes without being embodied. For example, an LLM using a calculator or database is using off-token processing, but that does not mean it has bodily experience.\n\nHowever, if an AI were connected to cameras, sensors, motors, and a robot body, some of its processing might be both **off-token** and related to something like **embodied cognition**. But the terms are not equivalent.",
